<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1436,858,1638]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1327,1351]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Note.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[320,416,1327,1351]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">paratype</typeStatus>
bears a label reading &quot;Type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirk." authorityName="Kirk." box="[768,952,1326,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Saccharodite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonoe">chrysonoe Kirk.</taxonomicName>
&quot; However from Kirkaldy's description it is clear that it shows no relationship to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirkaldy" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1906" box="[582,912,1362,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonoe">
<emphasis box="[582,802,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Rhotana chrysonoe</emphasis>
Kirkaldy
</taxonomicName>
, now 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirkaldy)" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Kirkaldy" box="[984,1386,1362,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Saccharodite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonoe">
<emphasis box="[984,1255,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Saccharodite chrysonoe</emphasis>
(Kirkaldy)
</taxonomicName>
, see that species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
